The Kenya Medical Practitioners and Dentists Board has urged the government to ban free medical camps that it has not certified. Board chairman George Magoha said some free medical camps offer substandard services, threatening lives. Addressing the 41st Kenya Obstetrical and Gynaecological Society annual scientific conference in Mombasa, he said the board will implement policies to ensure foreigners get certification before setting up any free camp.Magoha said some untrained personnel organise medical camps.&ldquo;People come into this country as if there is no government or regulator and organise camps all over, claimingthey are experts. We want to know and register you so we know what you are coming to do,&rdquo; he said. Magoha said the board is working round the clock to implement policies and ensure doctors do not charge patients exorbitantl